				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${}_\infty ^2[\eta - {\mathrm{MoTe}}_2{\mathrm{H}}_{{\mathrm{0}}{\mathrm{.125}}}]$$\end{document}∞2[η−MoTe2H0.125] yielding only real wavenumbers (with a lower bound 156 cm−1 and upper bound 1291 cm−1). The COSMO35 dielectric continuum solvation scheme was utilised in all calculations with parameters for water. More accurate single point energy evaluations of the obtained stationary points were calculated using a denser 5 × 9 k point grid on the optimised unit cells.

